{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17513551","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17513551"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T13:11:01+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T13:11:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12155"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12155","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12155"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.64,0.25,0.08,0,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4685"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78149"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4685","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4685"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12155"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63571"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"227"},{"type":"tags","id":"1243"},{"type":"tags","id":"4974"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"6281"},{"type":"tags","id":"11633"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7217"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7255"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26775"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78149","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78149"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 63-year-old woman presents to her general practice with four months of worsening right shoulder pain, especially at night. She has found it more difficult to hang the laundry and with changing clothes. She remembers injuring her shoulder about five months ago when she had knocked it on the kitchen shelf, after which she had some trouble reaching above her head. After about a month this began to worsen and has continued ever since. Her medical conditions include type 2 diabetes mellitus and hypothyroidism. On examination, she has a restricted range of active and passive external and internal rotation, but normal power. Movements are also painful. Neer test is negative.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Adhesive capsulitis","Rotator cuff injury","Subacromial impingement","C4/5 disc herniation","Osteoarthritis"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe presentation is likely that of \u003Cstrong\u003Eadhesive capsulitis\u003C/strong\u003E in the freezing phase which can last up to nine months. The hallmark on physical examination is reduced active and passive ROM. This is usually followed by the frozen phase comprising of improving pain with residual stiffness and subsequently by the thawing phase with a gradual increase in range of motion. Both of these phases are variable and can last for months. Risk factors include diabetes, hypothyroidism, an injury and prolonged immobilisation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERotator cuff injury \u003C/strong\u003Ewill typically have reduced active range of motion but no restriction on passive range of motion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubacromial impingement \u003C/strong\u003Eis caused by compression of the rotator cuff muscles by superior structures leading to inflammation and bursitis. It is the most common cause of shoulder pain. Neer and Hawkins test will be positive. These 2 tests are for subacromial impingement syndrome. Neer\u0027s test is performed by passively flexing the arm while it is internally rotated. The test is positive if the patient reports pain in this position. Hawkins test is performed by placing the patient\u0027s arm shoulder in 90 degrees of shoulder flexion with the elbow flexed to 90 degrees and then internally rotating the arm. It is positive if there is pain on internal rotation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EC4/5 disc herniation \u003C/strong\u003Ecan present as neuropathic pain, paraesthesia, and weakness in the deltoid muscles. However, there will not be restricted passive ROM.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOsteoarthritis \u003C/strong\u003Ein the shoulder would have pain worsened by activity and not specifically with overhead activity.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Adhesive capsulitis is a self-limiting disease with worse outcomes among diabetics.","Adhesive capsulitis is characterised by a progressive loss of both active and passive range of motion in the shoulder."],"references":["Mezian K, Coffey R, Chang KV. Frozen Shoulder. [Updated 2022 Jun 5]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2022 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK482162/","Creech JA, Silver S. Shoulder Impingement Syndrome. [Updated 2022 Apr 21]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2022 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK554518/","Ramirez J. Adhesive Capsulitis: Diagnosis and Management. Am Fam Physician. 2019 Mar 1;99(5):297-300. PMID: 30811157. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30811157/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63571"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12155"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63571","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63571"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-09T14:44:43+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-09T14:45:36+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"da